Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

R2 build surfaced a type-name mismatch touching every Phase 7 region
host that iterates JSON arrays. Chromium pin 148.0.7778.40 exposes
list-valued dict children as base::ListValue* (see base/values.h:43,
DictValue::FindList returns ListValue*); the hosts were typed with
the older base::Value::List* path which no longer exists at this
pin.

Files touched (R1 + R2 feature patches that shipped before any build
sanity check):
  slayzone_projects_host.cc     (patch 0018)
  slayzone_tools_host.cc        (patch 0019; also fixes a local
                                 base::Value::List params; → ListValue)
  slayzone_tasklist_host.cc     (patch 0021)
  slayzone_sidebar_host.cc      (patch 0021)
  slayzone_taskheader_host.cc   (patch 0021)

No behaviour change — pure type-spelling fix. Incremental build clean
after the change (525 targets rebuilt, Framework link ok).
